    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="480" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Pruyn</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 24.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States in
                                        Japan</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Kanagawa</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 17, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you of the
                            arrival of Sir Rutherford Alcock.</p>
                <p>I have had two very pleasant and satisfactory interviews with him, and
                            find that our views in relation to Japanese affairs are in entire
                            accord.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, very respectfully, your most obedient
                            servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ROBERT H. PRUYN, <hi rend="italic">Minister Resident in
                                    Japan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
